    "actions_taken": [
      "Mechanic evacuated to Teche Occupational Clinic in New Iberia, LA",
      "Incident verbally reported to BSEE Lafayette District at 5:28 PM on January 19, 2020",
      "Onsite investigation conducted by BSEE Lafayette District on January 24, 2020"
    ],
    "summary": "On January 19, 2020 at approximately 1400 hours, a mechanic was injured while descending a heliport stairway at Arena Offshore, LP operated facility EI238E. The mechanic, wearing a 50-pound backpack tool bag and carrying a 10-pound cardboard box, missed the final step while being escorted by a production operator. The mechanic fell forward, striking his head and torso on the handrail. The weight of the tool bag contributed to the severity of injuries. The mechanic was diagnosed with a bruised kidney and placed on light duty for 4 weeks.",
